<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 19 日星期五 21:11:44 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Republicans ‘Press Pause’ on Debt Ceiling Talks as June 1 Default Deadline Looms]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110469706" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:0:3055:2037_1440x900_80_0_1_be4b1f2dd09cb9835784cdba828bceef.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110397024" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/republicans-press-pause-on-debt-ceiling-talks-as-june-1-default-deadline-looms-1110469706.html?share-img=1110397024"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SAUL LOEB</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">3 月 17 日，美国总统乔·拜登在加利福尼亚州共和党众议院议长凯文·麦卡锡的陪同下，于圣帕特里克节一年一度的爱尔兰之友午餐会后离开华盛顿特区的美国国会大厦， 2023年</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="US President Joe Biden, accompanied by Speaker of the House Kevin McCarthy, Republican of California, departs after the annual Friends of Ireland luncheon on St. Patrick's Day at the US Capitol in Washington, DC, on March 17, 2023 - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="2023 年 3 月 17 日，美国总统乔·拜登在加利福尼亚州共和党众议院议长凯文·麦卡锡的陪同下，在圣帕特里克节一年一度的爱尔兰之友午餐会后离开华盛顿特区的美国国会大厦" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:160:3055:1878_1920x0_80_0_0_2df9847e7913bbfd9671274eea1ff55f.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:160:3055:1878_640x0_80_0_0_0ef54892a0a2c661ed7af1586d999ff0.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:160:3055:1878_1280x0_80_0_0_89209a56b5c316e66f3b9a8fc45df945.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:160:3055:1878_1920x0_80_0_0_2df9847e7913bbfd9671274eea1ff55f.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SAUL LOEB </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">芳汀嘉迪尼耶</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_gardinier_fantine/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">如果联邦政府无法拨出新的资金来偿还债务，它将违约，进一步损害其信用评级并引发经济危机。财政部警告说，违约最早可能在 6 月 1 日发生。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">周五，民主党控制的白宫和共和党控制的美国众议院之间的最新一轮谈判破裂，据报道共和党议员走出房间以示抗议。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “除非人们愿意就如何真正向前迈进并做正确的事情进行合理的对话，否则我们不会坐在这里自言自语，”众议员加勒特格雷夫斯 (R-LA) 告诉记者。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110469706" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/republicans-press-pause-on-debt-ceiling-talks-as-june-1-default-deadline-looms-1110469706.html?share-block=1110469708" data-title="“Until people are willing to have reasonable conversations about how you can actually move forward and do the right thing, then we’re not gonna sit here and talk to ourselves,” Rep. Garret Graves (R-LA) told reporters."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “我们决定暂停，因为它只是没有成效，”他补充说，并指出他不确定谈判是否会在周末恢复。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">由于共和党在众议院占多数，允许在 1 月中旬达到债务上限，而没有通过提高上限的法案，因此谈判基本上没有取得任何进展。新上任的众议院议长凯文麦卡锡 (R-CA) 采用了共和党的老策略，即利用违约威胁向民主党同事施压，要求他们接受在正常情况下他们可能不会同意的大幅削减预算。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “看，明年我们不能花更多的钱，”麦卡锡周五在罢工后告诉记者。 “我们必须比前一年花费更少。这很容易。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110469706" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/republicans-press-pause-on-debt-ceiling-talks-as-june-1-default-deadline-looms-1110469706.html?share-block=1110469711" data-title="“Look, we can’t be spending more money next year,” McCarthy told reporters on Friday after the walk-out. “We have to spend less than we spent the year before. It’s pretty easy.”"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">拜登继续坚称，他只会签署一项“干净”的债务上限法案——即在 2024 年预算中没有强制削减预算的法案，这是提高债务上限的典型方式。不过，本周早些时候，拜登和麦卡锡会晤后，两党成员都对达成妥协的可能性持乐观态度。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">国会在第一次世界大战期间设定了债务上限，通过批量而不是零碎地批准来简化拨款过程。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在上个世纪的大部分时间里，它没有任何政治重要性，但在 2011 年，共和党人引入了威胁允许违约的策略，以此作为阻碍平价医疗法案 (ACA) 的一种方式，这是一项广为人知的全面医疗保健法作为奥巴马医改。他们坚持认为联邦政府的预算赤字太大，唯一可以接受的缩减赤字的方法是削减开支，而不是增加税收。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="vrez"><div class="article__vrez"><div class="article__vrez-text"><p>美国财政部长珍妮特耶伦对即将发生的违约<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/congress-inaction-on-debt-limit-greatest-threat-to-us-economy-since-pandemic---treasury-1110424452.html" target="_blank">发出了可怕的警告</a></u>，违约最早可能在 6 月 1 日发生。周四，她在一次主要银行首席执行官会议上表示，如果政府违约，将产生“严重”的经济后果。</p></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 2011 年，当立法者在账户枯竭前几小时达成协议时，类似情况勉强避免触​​发违约，但标准普尔和穆迪仍因险些失败而下调华盛顿的信用评级。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">拜登目前正在日本参加七国集团峰会，但取消了剩余的亚洲之行，以便返回华盛顿参加债务上限谈判。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 20:30:08 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/republicans-press-pause-on-debt-ceiling-talks-as-june-1-default-deadline-looms-1110469706.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/republicans-press-pause-on-debt-ceiling-talks-as-june-1-default-deadline-looms-1110469706.html<category>经济</category><category>债务上限</category><category>美国债务上限危机</category><category>共和党人</category><category>凯文麦卡锡</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>僵局</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[German Defense Minister Wants Special Military Fund Spent Soon to Avoid Inflation Risks]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110469577" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109673104_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_349079b174caa3efcae39d26d25d09e6.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1109673086" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/german-defense-minister-wants-special-military-fund-spent-soon-to-avoid-inflation-risks-1110469577.html?share-img=1109673086"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Geert Vanden Wijngaert</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">德国国防部长鲍里斯·皮斯托瑞斯 (Boris Pistorius) 于 2023 年 3 月 20 日星期一抵达布鲁塞尔欧洲理事会大楼参加欧盟外交部长和国防部长会议时与媒体交谈。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Germany's Defense Minister Boris Pistorius speaks with the media as he arrives for a meeting of EU foreign and defense ministers at the European Council building in Brussels on Monday, March 20, 2023.  - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="2023 年 3 月 20 日星期一，德国国防部长鲍里斯·皮斯托瑞斯 (Boris Pistorius) 抵达布鲁塞尔欧洲理事会大楼参加欧盟外交部长和国防部长会议时与媒体交谈。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109673104_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_5eee2a84b3243ce14fe23bebddebf8ab.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109673104_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_0e81c7761d93c2b92de3b477533f2d4d.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109673104_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_34e9a2cdcd43f0b098cb88c4dc22dcb5.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/13/1109673104_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_5eee2a84b3243ce14fe23bebddebf8ab.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Geert Vanden Wijngaert </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据莫斯科（人造卫星）网报道：德国国防部长鲍里斯·皮斯托瑞斯周五表示，他打算尽快动用德国联邦国防军的 1000 亿欧元（1080 亿美元）特别基金，以免其购买力因通货膨胀而降低。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “我将坚持尽快花掉特别基金，以尽可能少地被通货膨胀吞噬。我还打算增加国防部在联邦预算中的份额”他在接受德国媒体采访时说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位部长补充说，在乌克兰持续不断的冲突中，必须重新定义该国武装部队的作用。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">皮斯托瑞斯说：“我们来自和平时期的红利生活，[北约]联盟和国防不那么重要的时代。现在一切都变了，我们必须适应。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110469577" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/german-defense-minister-wants-special-military-fund-spent-soon-to-avoid-inflation-risks-1110469577.html?share-block=1110469580" data-title="&quot;We come from the times when we lived on dividends of the peaceful time and when the [NATO] Alliance and the national defense were less important. Now everything has changed again, and we have to adapt,&quot; Pistorius said.  "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 6月，德国议会和联邦委员会以多数票通过了德国总理奥拉夫·舒尔茨提出的设立1000亿欧元专项基金以提高国家防务能力的倡议，使德军成为欧洲最大的正规军。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> 1月27日，皮斯托瑞斯对德国媒体表示，特别国防基金不足以让德国实现军队现代化和支付军事装备的维修费用。随后，有媒体报道称，皮斯托瑞斯曾呼吁德国武装部队的年度预算每年增加100亿欧元。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 20:00:34 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/german-defense-minister-wants-special-military-fund-spent-soon-to-avoid-inflation-risks-1110469577.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/german-defense-minister-wants-special-military-fund-spent-soon-to-avoid-inflation-risks-1110469577.html<category>军队</category><category>鲍里斯·皮斯托瑞斯</category><category>德国</category><category>德国联邦国防军</category><category>通货膨胀</category><category>防御</category><category>运营成本</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden Admin Wages Information War Against Americans to Fund Ukraine Conflict]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110469223" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3072:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_49e118e38df9d3eef4f6ec6fb067fc98.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1109779082" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/biden-admin-wages-information-war-against-americans-to-fund-ukraine-conflict-1110469223.html?share-img=1109779082"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / LIBKOS</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">Украинские военные с гаубицей M777。 Архивное фото</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Украинские военные с гаубицей M777. Архивное фото - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="Украинские военные с гаубицей M777。 Архивное фото" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3073:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_7dd3b13fccf72222ef1053bec2d7cf6d.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3073:1728_640x0_80_0_0_cbcd9ef950ed12986e002348f069bf24.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3073:1728_1280x0_80_0_0_90faade0c32f646d294dee7be600bfde.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/04/17/1109779241_0:0:3073:1728_1920x0_80_0_0_7dd3b13fccf72222ef1053bec2d7cf6d.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / LIBKOS </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">美国向基辅提供的大量军事援助已经引起了美国人的重大担忧，白宫花费数十亿美元资助其针对俄罗斯的代理人战争。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据最近的报道，由于五角大楼使用重置成本而不是实际武器成本来对武器进行估价，因此会计错误导致美国高估了运往乌克兰的物资高达 30 亿美元。国防部官员实际上在两个月前就发现了这个问题，但现在才通知国会，这激怒了立法者。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这些报告很容易在<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/biden-deal-with-republicans-over-debt-ceiling-would-reward-hostage-taking-1110461153.html" target="_blank">债务上限陷入僵局</a>之际出现，因为“腾出”数十亿美元让拜登不必向国会要求<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/report-ukraine-has-five-months-to-impress-us-before-being-pressured-into-peace-talks-1110453032.html" target="_blank">为乌克兰军事援助提供额外资金</a>。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">但是，这个“小错误”究竟说明了华盛顿的问责制及其在违约迫在眉睫的情况下涉及纳税人资金时的优先事项？</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> EMP 特别工作组学者、前美国国防部官员<strong>戴维·T·派恩 (David T. Pyne)</strong>在接受人造卫星采访时解释了这一令人不安的发现背后的确切原因。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>人造卫星：30亿美元的误算怎么可能？</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>戴维·T·派恩：</strong>鉴于乌克兰报告美国迄今提供了 1960 亿美元的援助，这个数额是乌克兰 2021 年国防预算的 33 倍，而且远远超过其整个 2022 年的国内生产总值，我认为有可能对这个规模做出错误的估计。到目前为止，美国对乌克兰的经济和军事援助几乎没有任何问责制，因为美国国会没有采取任何措施来监督援助的使用情况。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">哥伦比亚广播公司新闻报道称，只有大约 30% 的西方军事援助到达了乌克兰的前线部队，其余大部分援助<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230423/sy-hersh-west-knows-ukraine-weapons-end-up-on-black-market-1109774596.html" target="_blank">都在黑市上出售</a>，以充实包括泽伦斯基总统在内的腐败乌克兰官僚的腰包。报告可能已将高达数亿美元的美国援助收入囊中。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>人造卫星：你认为五角大楼为什么等了两个月才告诉国会？</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>戴维·T·派恩：</strong>我认为我们已经看到拜登政府发表了许多欺骗性言论，旨在欺骗美国人民了解其针对俄罗斯的代理人战争的真相，因为他们知道关于战争起源的难以忽视的真相，事实上，无论<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/us-reportedly-unconvinced-kiev-needs-expensive-f-16s-amid-wests-schism-over-jet-supplies-1110433307.html" target="_blank">美国提供多少军事支持</a>，乌克兰都没有机会赢得它，民众对战争的支持将大大减少。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">因此，五角大楼试图在两个月的时间内向国会隐瞒这一重大会计错误，这一点也不让我感到惊讶。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>人造卫星：这件事有多反常？像这样的误算经常发生吗？这么重大的错误，五角大楼两个月不告诉国会，这正常吗？</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <strong>David T. Pyne：</strong>我自 2005 年以来就没有在国防部工作过，所以我不确定这个会计错误有多正常或有多频繁，但毫无疑问，国会利用这一事件通过法律让美国国防部变得重要是很重要的国防部比现在对国会更加负责，以确保它不会再次发生。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>人造卫星：一名高级国防官员告诉路透社，这一错误“可能会导致更多武器被运往基辅以防御俄罗斯军队。”您是否认为五角大楼有人故意高估了援助，以便向乌克兰运送更多武器？</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <strong>David T. Pyne：</strong>是的，我认为这是很有可能的。拜登政府担心共和党领导的众议院可能不会批准其提议的乌克兰援助计划，因此它可能正在想方设法欺骗国会提供数十亿美元的直接军事援助，根据国防部的说法，目前这一援助已超过 370 亿美元。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">拜登政府的高级官员基本上一直在对美国人民发动信息战、虚假信息和观念管理运动，以让他们<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230518/russian-strike-eliminates-massive-stock-of-foreign-weapons-and-ammo-in-ukraine-1110442643.html" target="_blank">支持乌克兰的战争</a>，这场战争是为了反对美国的国家安全利益而进行的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">话虽如此，我确实认为，在整个历史上，世界各国政府宣传其公民支持损害自身利益的战争是非常普遍的，因此拜登政府的欺骗性战争宣传活动在这方面并不是独一无二的。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>俄罗斯卫星通讯社：您认为这一事件对未来对乌克兰的供应有什么影响吗？您是否希望五角大楼的人员下次在处理数字时更加严格？</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>戴维·T·派恩：</strong>我希望这一事件能让国会议员暂停向乌克兰提供任何额外援助，直到我们迄今为止向他们提供的援助完全负责为止。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，鉴于民主党仍然控制着美国参议院，而且许多众议院共和党高层仍然支持单方面解除美国军队的武装，以便向乌克兰运送数千个更先进的武器系统，我怀疑它是否会这样做。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 18:17:04 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/biden-admin-wages-information-war-against-americans-to-fund-ukraine-conflict-1110469223.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/biden-admin-wages-information-war-against-americans-to-fund-ukraine-conflict-1110469223.html<category>分析</category><category>我们</category><category>乌克兰危机</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>军事援助</category><category>美国军事援助</category><category>五角大楼</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Yellen Says More Bank Mergers Probably Necessary - Report]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110469015" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110258871_0:0:3073:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_7466764a971527bcf88936b8f6f27b27.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110258853" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/yellen-says-more-bank-mergers-probably-necessary---report-1110469015.html?share-img=1110258853"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SHUJI KAJIYAMA</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">美国财政部长珍妮特·耶伦于 2023 年 5 月 11 日在新泻 Toki Messe 举行的 G7 财长和央行行长会议新闻发布会上发表讲话</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="US Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen&nbsp;speaks during a press conference at the G7 meeting of Finance Ministers and Central Bank Governors at Toki Messe in Niigata on May 11, 2023 - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="2023 年 5 月 11 日，美国财政部长珍妮特·耶伦在新泻 Toki Messe 举行的 G7 财长和央行行长会议新闻发布会上发表讲话" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110258871_0:159:3073:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_0a4f3610b4ae0bcde97fe5e0278d017a.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110258871_0:159:3073:1888_640x0_80_0_0_d4418e1fe1821f22672b0dc11be3e6eb.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110258871_0:159:3073:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_af9702c86714a461dc6d3c11fc122e35.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/0b/1110258871_0:159:3073:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_0a4f3610b4ae0bcde97fe5e0278d017a.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> ©<a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">法新社 2023</a> / SHUJI KAJIYAMA </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">芳汀嘉迪尼耶</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_gardinier_fantine/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">拜登政府已进行干预，阻止了几项企业收购，包括捷蓝航空试图收购精神航空公司和微软试图收购视频游戏制造商动视暴雪。然而，当谈到该国最大的金融机构时，它却唱出了不同的调子。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据知情人士透露，美国财政部长珍妮特耶伦在与该国最大银行的首席执行官会面时表示，随着金融危机的继续蔓延，可能有必要进行更多的银行合并。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">据报道，耶伦是在周四与银行政策研究所的一次会议上发表上述言论的，该研究所由摩根大通的杰米戴蒙、美国银行的布莱恩莫伊尼汉、高盛的大卫所罗门以及其他十几位银行首席执行官组成。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110469015" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/yellen-says-more-bank-mergers-probably-necessary---report-1110469015.html?share-block=1110469017" data-title="Yellen reportedly made the remarks in a Thursday meeting with the Bank Policy Institute, a collection of bank CEOs that includes Jamie Dimon of JPMorgan Chase, Brian Moynihan of Bank of America, David Solomon of Goldman Sachs, and more than a dozen others."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> <u><a href="https://home.treasury.gov/news/press-releases/jy1492" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">财政部对会议的宣读</a></u>称，耶伦“重申了美国银行体系的实力和稳健性”，但没有提及合并的话题。然而，这位前美联储主席在本周早些时候对媒体的评论中确实提到了他们。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p>耶伦对美国媒体说：“这可能是一个我们将看到更多合并的环境，而且你知道，我认为监管机构将对此持开放态度，如果发生的话。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110469015" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/yellen-says-more-bank-mergers-probably-necessary---report-1110469015.html?share-block=1110469019" data-title="&amp;quot;This might be an environment in which we’re going to see more mergers, and you know, that’s something I think the regulators will be open to, if it occurs,&amp;quot; Yellen told US media."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">本月早些时候，联邦存款保险公司 (FDIC) 将 First Republic Bank 的大部分股份<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230502/us-banking-crisis-nearly-over-after-jpmorgan-chase-scoops-up-first-republic-in-auction-1110017848.html">卖给了摩根大通</a></u>，这是一家政府所有的公司，用于保护储户的资金免受银行挤兑的影响，在几周前的收购后进行了一次大甩卖。 First Republic 的倒闭是美国历史上第二大银行倒闭，紧随几周前的第三大银行硅谷银行倒闭。只有华盛顿互惠银行在 2008 年股市崩盘期间的倒闭规模更大。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">允许美国最大银行摩根大通接管第一共和国大部分资产的决定遭到美国总统拜登的反合并盟友的严厉批评。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “这里发生的事情是因为银行监管不足并开始倒闭，联邦政府帮助摩根大通变得更大，”美国参议员伊丽莎白沃伦（D-MA）告诉记者。 “今天可能看起来不错，但一切都在飞速发展，但最终，如果摩根大通等大型银行之一开始跌跌撞撞，美国纳税人将成为风险承担者。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110469015" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/yellen-says-more-bank-mergers-probably-necessary---report-1110469015.html?share-block=1110469023" data-title="&amp;quot;What happened here is because a bank was under-regulated and started to fail, the federal government has helped JPMorgan Chase get even bigger,&amp;quot; US Sen. Elizabeth Warren (D-MA) told reporters. &amp;quot;It may look good today while everything’s flying high, but ultimately if one of those giant banks, JPMorgan Chase, starts to stumble, the American taxpayers are the ones who will be on the line.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">然而，拜登政府在危机期间也没有完全迁就金融家：在硅谷银行和 Signature 银行 3 月份倒闭后，拜登表示投资者将无法享受受保存款持有人通过 FDIC 获得的保护。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “银行的投资者将不会受到保护，”拜登告诉记者。 “他们故意冒险，当风险没有得到回报时，投资者就会赔钱。这就是资本主义的运作方式。” </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110469015" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/yellen-says-more-bank-mergers-probably-necessary---report-1110469015.html?share-block=1110469025" data-title="&amp;quot;Investors in the banks will not be protected,&amp;quot; Biden told reporters. &amp;quot;They knowingly took a risk and when the risk didn’t pay off, the investors lose their money. That’s how capitalism works.&amp;quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">政府试图在危机中营造出一种稳定的形象，而此时美联储已经提高利率一年多以减缓通货膨胀。 4月下旬<u><a href="https://www.bea.gov/news/2023/gross-domestic-product-first-quarter-2023-advance-estimate">公布的经济数据</a></u>显示，2023年第一季度美国国内生产总值（GDP）仅增长1.1%，较上一季度2.6%的增速大幅放缓。经济预测人士预测，随着时间的推移，美国经济将进一步放缓，预计 2023 年 GDP 增长率仅为 0.7%。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">耶伦还就联邦立法者正在进行的一场高风险的金融小鸡游戏的结果<u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230517/congress-inaction-on-debt-limit-greatest-threat-to-us-economy-since-pandemic---treasury-1110424452.html">发出了可怕的警告</a></u>，他们四个月来未能打破僵局并提高债务上限。这位财政部长表示，如果不提高上限，美国最早可能在 6 月 1 日违约，这将破坏该国的信用评级并引发经济危机。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110469015" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/yellen-says-more-bank-mergers-probably-necessary---report-1110469015.html?share-block=1110469028" data-title="Yellen has also issued dire warnings about the outcome of a high-stakes game of financial chicken being played by federal lawmakers, who have failed for four months to break an impasse and raise the debt ceiling. The Treasury chief said the US could default on its debts as soon as June 1 if the ceiling is not raised, which would destroy the country’s credit rating and trigger an economic crisis."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">即使美国避免违约，这场危机也可能导致国际观察家下调联邦政府的信用评级，就像 2011 年类似危机期间发生的那样。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 17:38:40 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/yellen-says-more-bank-mergers-probably-necessary---report-1110469015.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/yellen-says-more-bank-mergers-probably-necessary---report-1110469015.html<category>美洲</category><category>银行</category><category>企业合并</category><category>珍妮特·耶伦</category><category>我们</category><category>第一共和国银行</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Shrapnel-Flinging Airbags Could Trigger Largest-Ever Car Recall in US History]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110466984" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105767/91/1057679114_0:0:4113:2588_1440x900_80_0_1_089a049c5e8f8ab28e0591f71e157e55.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1057679113" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/shrapnel-flinging-airbags-could-trigger-largest-ever-car-recall-in-us-history-1110466984.html?share-img=1057679113"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Paul Sancya，文件 /</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">在这张 2010 年 11 月 30 日的文件照片中，一名生产线工人在密歇根州哈姆特拉克的通用汽车哈姆特拉克装配厂检查车辆。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt=" In this Nov. 30, 2010 file photo, a line worker checks vehicles at the General Motors Hamtramck assembly plant in Hamtramck, Mich. - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="在这张 2010 年 11 月 30 日的档案照片中，一名生产线工人在密歇根州哈姆特拉克的通用汽车哈姆特拉克组装厂检查车辆。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105767/91/1057679114_0:147:4113:2461_1920x0_80_0_0_f0d7b10064cbe45255e2a3effc0178ba.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105767/91/1057679114_0:147:4113:2461_640x0_80_0_0_48256fd7ad927896e67e3242a0adb8fe.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105767/91/1057679114_0:147:4113:2461_1280x0_80_0_0_d30944e4754905178d442d293dba9a0f.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/105767/91/1057679114_0:147:4113:2461_1920x0_80_0_0_f0d7b10064cbe45255e2a3effc0178ba.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © AP Photo / Paul Sancya，档案 / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">芳汀嘉迪尼耶</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_gardinier_fantine/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据美国媒体报道，美国联邦安全监管机构的一项调查发现，约有 6700 万个安全气囊存在缺陷，这些安全气囊在充气时能够向汽车内部发射弹片。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据报道，美国国家公路交通安全局 (NHTSA) 已敦促 ARC Automotive 召回 2000 年至 2018 年间生产的约 6700 万个安全气囊充气机，但这家总部位于田纳西州的制造商迄今拒绝这样做。在上周致美国国家公路交通安全管理局的一封信中，ARC 声称它被召回要求“证明是负面的”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"><p> “当广泛的现场测试没有发现任何固有缺陷时，我们不同意 NHTSA 的新要求，”ARC 在上周的一份声明中表示。 </p></div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110466984" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/shrapnel-flinging-airbags-could-trigger-largest-ever-car-recall-in-us-history-1110466984.html?share-block=1110466986" data-title="&amp;quot;We disagree with NHTSA&amp;#x27;s new sweeping request when extensive field testing has found no inherent defect,&amp;quot; ARC said in a statement last week."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">自 2014 年以来，至少有两人因 ARC 安全气囊在充气时向汽车发射弹片而丧生。其中一位是 10 个孩子的母亲，她于 2021 年在密歇根州上半岛的一场车祸中丧生，这起车祸被描述为轻微车祸，只是在她的安全气囊充气时金属充气机碎片击中了她的脖子。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">据美国媒体报道，50 种不同型号的约 680 万辆汽车可能受到召回的影响，尽管随着 NHTSA 向 ARC 施压召回，这一数字很容易上升。受影响的品牌包括奥迪、通用汽车、现代、福特、大众和宝马，每个品牌也可以选择单独召回。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110466984" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/shrapnel-flinging-airbags-could-trigger-largest-ever-car-recall-in-us-history-1110466984.html?share-block=1110466989" data-title="According to US media, some 6.8 million vehicles across 50 different models could be affected by a recall, although that number could easily rise as the NHTSA presses ARC to issue a recall. Affected brands include Audi, General Motors, Hyundai, Ford, Volkswagen, and BMW, each of which could also choose to issue its own recalls separately."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> ARC 也不是唯一一家因安全气囊缺陷而面临召回的安全气囊制造商。去年 11 月， <u><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20221118/tesla-recalls-nearly-30000-model-x-cars-over-airbag-issue-us-road-safety-authority-1104405388.html">特斯拉还召回了</a></u>30,000 个安全气囊，指出它们可能在低速碰撞中充气不当。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国历史上最大规模的汽车召回是由日本高田公司生产的有缺陷的安全气囊引发的，该安全气囊在充气时还导致金属碎片爆炸进入车内。在 NHTSA 下令召回美国道路上的 4200 万辆汽车后，高田于 2017 年申请破产。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 16:38:16 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/shrapnel-flinging-airbags-could-trigger-largest-ever-car-recall-in-us-history-1110466984.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/shrapnel-flinging-airbags-could-trigger-largest-ever-car-recall-in-us-history-1110466984.html<category>美洲</category><category>通用汽车</category><category>现代</category><category>安全气囊</category><category>记起</category><category>我们</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden Deal With Republicans Over Debt Ceiling Would 'Reward Hostage-Taking']]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110461153" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:0:3055:2037_1440x900_80_0_1_be4b1f2dd09cb9835784cdba828bceef.jpg?source-sid=afp" data-photoview-image-id="1110397024" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/biden-deal-with-republicans-over-debt-ceiling-would-reward-hostage-taking-1110461153.html?share-img=1110397024"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SAUL LOEB</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">3 月 17 日，美国总统乔·拜登在加利福尼亚州共和党众议院议长凯文·麦卡锡的陪同下，于圣帕特里克节一年一度的爱尔兰之友午餐会后离开华盛顿特区的美国国会大厦， 2023年</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="afp" alt="US President Joe Biden, accompanied by Speaker of the House Kevin McCarthy, Republican of California, departs after the annual Friends of Ireland luncheon on St. Patrick's Day at the US Capitol in Washington, DC, on March 17, 2023 - Sputnik International, 1920, 19.05.2023" title="2023 年 3 月 17 日，美国总统乔·拜登在加利福尼亚州共和党众议院议长凯文·麦卡锡的陪同下，在圣帕特里克节一年一度的爱尔兰之友午餐会后离开华盛顿特区的美国国会大厦" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:160:3055:1878_1920x0_80_0_0_2df9847e7913bbfd9671274eea1ff55f.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:160:3055:1878_640x0_80_0_0_0ef54892a0a2c661ed7af1586d999ff0.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:160:3055:1878_1280x0_80_0_0_89209a56b5c316e66f3b9a8fc45df945.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/10/1110397042_0:160:3055:1878_1920x0_80_0_0_2df9847e7913bbfd9671274eea1ff55f.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © <a href="https://ria.ru/docs/about/copyright_afp.html" title="法新社 2023">AFP 2023</a> / SAUL LOEB </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-image"><img media-type="s150x150" data-source-sid="not_sputnik_photo" alt="James Tweedie - Sputnik International" title="詹姆斯·特威迪" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/08/1c/1080307270_0:3:397:400_100x100_80_0_0_7777393b9b18802f2e3c5eaa9cbcc612.png" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">詹姆斯·特威迪</div><div class="article__author-links"> <a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_tweedie_james/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a> <a data-modal-open="feedback_author" href="mailto:j.tweedie@sputniknews.com" title="写给作者">写给作者</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">民主党人乔·拜登和共和党领导人正试图在 6 月 1 日关键时刻之前就取消政府借款上限达成协议。康奈尔大学法学教授、韦斯特伍德资本高级顾问罗伯特·霍克特博士将这次反对与内战时期的反对进行了比较邦联叛军。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">一位学者表示，美国总统乔·拜登正在与共和党人谈判提高债务上限，以迎合“白人至上主义者”和“劫持人质者”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">本周早些时候，在 G7 峰会召开之前，拜登缺席了在悉尼举行的由澳大利亚、印度和日本组成的“四方”亚太国家集团峰会，与共和党众议院议长凯文麦卡锡就提高联邦借款上限从 1.1 万亿美元提高到 1.5 万亿美元。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">共和党人希望政府削减公共支出，以换取更多借贷的许可。但财政部长珍妮特耶伦警告称，如果危机未能在 6 月 1 日之前得到解决，它可能会拖欠现有债务或社会保障金。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">罗伯特·霍克特博士告诉<a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/why-is-joe-biden-entertaining-republican-austerity-proposals-1110448028.html" target="_blank">人造卫星，</a>他对跨党派会谈“非常担心”。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">霍克特说：“我不确定拜登是否真的会与这些反动派妥协，他们实际上是在劫持人质。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110461153" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/biden-deal-with-republicans-over-debt-ceiling-would-reward-hostage-taking-1110461153.html?share-block=1110467199" data-title="&quot;I'm not sure whether Biden might actually be compromising with some of these reactionaries who are, in effect, hostage taking,&quot; Hockett said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位学者强调，不提高借贷上限将使政府无法支付已经编入预算并获得批准的项目。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “我们在这里谈论的债务已经欠下了。这是立法债务。这基本上是去年国会通过预算的结果。因此，实际上，众议院共和党核心小组的这个残余派系正在做的是威胁要违约或违约其自己招致的债务，从而当然会灾难性地摧毁美国经济。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110461153" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/biden-deal-with-republicans-over-debt-ceiling-would-reward-hostage-taking-1110461153.html?share-block=1110463229" data-title="&quot;The debt that we're talking about here is already owed. That is legislated debt. That is essentially the upshot of last year's Congress-passed budget. So, in effect, with this rump faction of the Republican caucus in the House of Representatives is doing is threatening to renege or to default on its own debt that it itself incurred, thereby, of course, catastrophically destroying the American economy.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位法学教授甚至将拜登与共和党领导人的会谈比作与恐怖分子谈判的政客。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">霍克特说：“在我看来，拜登可能会妥协或实际上是在奖励劫持人质，如果他以任何方式与这些人妥协，他就是在奖励绑架者。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110461153" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230519/biden-deal-with-republicans-over-debt-ceiling-would-reward-hostage-taking-1110461153.html?share-block=1110467200" data-title="&quot;It seems to me that Biden might be compromising with or in effect, rewarding hostage taking, and he is rewarding kidnapers if he compromises in any way with these people,&quot; Hockett said."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">他担心正在讨论的妥协可能包括“令人难以置信的严厉削减各种形式的社会支出，这些支出使各种非富裕的美国人受益。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位评论员说，拜登正在与“白人至上主义的新同盟者、吉姆·克劳共和党人”交谈是“可怕的”——忘记了<strong>民主党</strong>是奴隶制和吉姆·克劳种族隔离法的政党。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">霍克特说，对进步派人士的另一种恐惧是，“拜登会像他在 2019 年首次宣布上任时一样可怕，就像我们许多人担心的那样”，尽管他们“看到他可能不是”而感到松了一口气。那是他入主白宫后真正开始做一些体面的事情的时候。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>如需对时事的更多分析，请关注我们的人造卫星电台节目<em><a href="https://sputnikglobe.com/radio_by_any_means/" target="_blank">“不择手段”。</a></em></strong></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 19 May 2023 15:58:10 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/biden-deal-with-republicans-over-debt-ceiling-would-reward-hostage-taking-1110461153.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230519/biden-deal-with-republicans-over-debt-ceiling-would-reward-hostage-taking-1110461153.html<category>美洲</category><category>美国债务上限危机</category><category>债务上限</category><category>我们</category><category>美国联邦储备银行</category><category>凯文麦卡锡</category><category>乔·拜登</category><category>白色的房子</category><category>共和党人</category><category>吉姆克劳</category><category>康奈尔大学</category></item></channel></rss>